
// This Hyperlambda code constructs a connection string by concatenating a generic connection string prefix with a database name extracted from the [.arguments] node. The [set-value] slot assigns this concatenated string to the [.connection] node, using [strings.concat] to combine the static "[generic|" prefix, the value of the [database] argument, and the closing "]" bracket.
set-value:x:@.connection
   strings.concat
      .:[generic|
      get-value:x:@.arguments/*/database
      .:]
